I'm posting from LJTalk, which right now makes little sense to me. XD So, just posting to see if it works.

Wow, I haven't updated in forever. I guess no one ever has to worry about me flooding their flist. XD;

School has taken over my life. Seriously. ;__; I barely have time for anything else. Anyway, I got a bunch of bases and textures and things for icons, so I'm hoping I'll be able to make some kind of icons while working on two projects due after my Fall Break.

I now have a absolutely beautiful layout! :D

Highschool's been pretty good, actually. Lot of homework, but that's all. No drama. Yet. XD

Signed up for Drama Club, LMAO, but it'll be pretty good.

LOL, EVEN THOUGH I TOLD SAKURA I HATED DRAMA. I TAKE IT BAAACK.

I miss Fullmetal Alchemist. Seriously. Like, I haven't seen it in about 6 weeks now. I died inside a little. :D I watched the DVD the other day, and it made me really sad. I can't watch that show without, just, overflowing with emotion...

Anyway, mesna is my anti-drug and i'm unna eat choo. XD I LOVE YOU ALL.

So.
School tomorrow.

<font color="#800000" size="1">love just doesn't make sense, does it?</font>

Those fingertips touched
And lit up this heart
A melody streams out
It wishes love

The end of a wounded branch
Is its fate only to decay?

In the loopholes of times chained together
A small drop of light went astray

The end of this dream is wishing to face only you

Silver moonlight
Reflects in these eyes
This peaceful melody
Please, make it last forever

The sound of a pointer engraving time
Is its fate never to argue?

Sworn, these illusions were wrapped up
A spiral of blank light

All it is seeking is an ending of happiness

In the loopholes of time coloured with glass
Drops of calm light rise

The end of this dream is wishing to find only that

Hikari no Rasenritsu [Melody of Light] Translated from Japanese

GUESS WHAT.

I saw and talked to the police, hana, and rachel crowe today! =D

See, alright, I was sitting in the car in the parking lot waiting for my mom to come out of rack room shoes, 'cause I didn't wanna go inside. Sooo then I looked up one time from my cellphone and saw this guy running across the parking lot. I was like...why is he running...? Then I thought, OH. He's stealing something. My sister saw it too, so we just stared at him run across the parking lot with a shoe box while this lady that worked at rack room chased him. I called my mom and was like, "did someone just come running out of rack room?" and she said, "DID YOU SEE HIM?!!?!?!" and i said, ".....yeah." SO, she made me come talk to the police and give them a description of the burglar. It was fun, ROFL. I felt so stupid though, just standing there talking to this random police officer about a man who just ran across the parking lot with shoes. -_-'

.....

The Fuhrer killed his son and the Fuhrer stabbed Roy a couple of times then Al sacrificed himself for his brother and i guess Dante got eaten by Gluttony (YAY!) and then Roy came out of the Estate (the Fuhrer got killed by Roy WOOP Roy: King Bradley, how many times must I kill you...before you die) with  the Fuhrer's dead son and then that #$%^&*@#$%^& Terminarcher came and Riza Hawkeye came up behind Robo-Archer and shot him like 10 times WOO and I think the bullet passed through Archer and hit Roy or Archer shot Roy in the eye before Riza got up there to shoot him. Then Envy the crossdresser went through the Gate thing and turned into a dragon thing (what the freak happened there....?) and was lost forever and Ed was there and he cried for Al. So then the now alive Ed who was resurrected by Al was back to normal and Al was gone. And so Edward woke up crying with Rose in his face saying how Al sacrificed himself. So then Ed gave himself up for Al.

*commercial break*

*takes deep breath*

And then so Al ends up as his old self- a ten year old boy with no memories of his past. And it shows a bookwork named Sheska who works in the military library writing a letter to Winry about the goings-on of Central. (this is at a later date) Rose's son had grown up, Al is normal, and Winry is grown up. Ed and Al's old teacher comes to dinner with them and Al, for the 3rd time, asks if he can learn alchemy to bring Edward back.

Teacher: " How could I ever say no to a face like that?"

and it showed how Ed crossed over the Gate, into our alchemy-less world, in Munich, 1925. He wants to talk to a scholar from Transylvania about a rocket that can go into outer space. He believes that Gate is up there, so he can return to his brother in his own world. It ends with them reaching into the sky. 

And then I started to bawl my eyes out. OHMAN. IT WAS SAD. 

OH! AND I SAW THIS MORNING THE EPISODES START OVER AT EPISODE 1 NEXT WEEK and the same time! If you can't stay up that late, tape it! It's worth it. Trust me. =D

Metal is a unique Element; strong and unyielding
yet flexible and diverse as well. Metal
Elemental individuals reflect this in their
unique and pragmatic outlook on life. They
are possessed by frugality, never willing to
spend more than is necessary, whether the
cost is money, time, or something else. They
are also somewhat minimalist because of this,
choosing their ideas and items based on
practicality rather than style or appearance.
They have a very powerful will, usually
manifesting itself as duty and honor;
promises made to others take precedence over
all else. They are also capable of changing
and adapting to a wide range of situations or
environments, but this adaptation is often
not caused by their own decisions. Metal
individuals sometimes come to adopt the
ideals, styles, and mannerisms of those
around them, without even noticing or
understanding why. They express themselves
through manual creativity, becoming highly
inclined toward machines and technology, as
well as being able to create arts and crafts
with their hands.

What is your dominant Element? (A serious personality test, for a change)
